members.name: Ayesha Khan
members.bio:
Passionate about building tech communities and empowering students to explore Google technologies. With over 3 years of experience in organizing tech events, I love connecting developers and fostering innovation.

I believe in the power of community-driven learning and have helped organize over 20+ workshops and hackathons. When I'm not organizing events, you can find me exploring new web technologies or mentoring fellow developers.

projects.name: GDG Community Platform
projects.description: Developed a web platform to manage GDG events, member registrations, and community interactions. Built with React and Firebase.

projects.name: Tech Mentorship Program
projects.description: Launched a mentorship initiative connecting senior developers with newcomers, resulting in 50+ successful mentorship pairs.

projects.name: Women in Tech Workshop Series
projects.description: Organized quarterly workshops focused on encouraging women participation in technology fields.

members.name: Bilal Ahmed
members.bio:
Full-stack web developer with expertise in modern web technologies. I'm passionate about creating beautiful, functional websites and teaching others the art of web development.

I specialize in React, Node.js, and cloud technologies. I've been coding for over 4 years and love sharing knowledge through workshops and code reviews.

projects.name: E-Commerce Platform
projects.description: Built a full-featured e-commerce platform with payment integration, user authentication, and admin dashboard using MERN stack.

projects.name: GDG Website Redesign
projects.description: Led the complete redesign of the GDG Wah Campus website, improving user experience and mobile responsiveness.

projects.name: Web Development Bootcamp
projects.description: Conducted intensive 6-week web development bootcamp for 30+ students covering HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and React.

members.name: Fatima Ali
members.bio:
Android developer passionate about creating innovative mobile applications. I love exploring the latest Android development trends and sharing knowledge with the community.

With 3+ years of Android development experience, I've built several apps that have helped local businesses digitize their operations.

projects.name: Campus Navigator App
projects.description: Developed an Android app to help new students navigate the campus, find classrooms, and connect with peers.

projects.name: Local Business Directory
projects.description: Created a comprehensive business directory app for local Wah businesses with ratings, reviews, and contact features.

projects.name: Android Study Group
projects.description: Organized weekly Android development study sessions, helping 25+ students learn mobile development.

members.name: Saad Malik
members.bio:
Cloud architect and AI enthusiast with deep expertise in Google Cloud Platform and machine learning. I'm passionate about helping developers leverage cloud technologies to build scalable applications.

I hold multiple Google Cloud certifications and enjoy exploring the intersection of AI and cloud computing.

projects.name: ML-Powered Study Assistant

projects.name: Cloud Migration Workshop Series
